Motion Detection Web App — Setup Guide
Project Structure
```
motion-web/
├── backend/
│   └── app.py          ← Flask backend (your motion detection)
└── frontend/
    └── App.jsx         ← React dashboard
```
---
1. Backend Setup (Python + Flask)
Install dependencies
```bash
pip install flask flask-cors opencv-python imutils
```
Run the server
```bash
python app.py
```
The backend starts at: http://localhost:5000
API Endpoints
Method	Route	Description
GET	`/video_feed`	MJPEG live stream
GET	`/status`	JSON: status, fps, motion count
POST	`/start`	Start camera
POST	`/stop`	Stop camera
POST	`/reset`	Reset background reference frame
---
2. Frontend Setup (React)
Create a new React app
```bash
npm create vite@latest motion-frontend -- --template react
cd motion-frontend
```
Replace src/App.jsx with the provided App.jsx
Run the frontend
```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```
Opens at: http://localhost:5173
---
Tips
Camera not working? Change `cv2.VideoCapture(0)` to `1` or `2` in `app.py`
Reset Background — use this when lighting changes and false motion appears
The frontend polls `/status` every 500ms for live stats
The video stream uses MJPEG (no WebSocket needed)
---
Features
✅ Live video stream in browser
✅ Real-time motion detection with bounding boxes
✅ FPS counter
✅ Motion event log
✅ Start / Stop / Reset controls
✅ Alert indicator when motion is detected